  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 29 for SLE 15 SP1)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.12.14-197_108 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2022-27666: Fixed a buffer overflow vulnerability in IPsec ESP transformation code. This flaw allowed a local attacker with a normal user privilege to overwrite kernel heap objects and may cause a local privilege escalation. (bnc#1197462)\n- CVE-2022-22942: Fixed stale file descriptors on failed usercopy. (bsc#1195065)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
